                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d60">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 2413/141.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Rockhill</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-07-20">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 20, 1908</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Edict to-day gives T’ang Shao-yi rank of president of a board and appoints him
                    special envoy to the United States to express the thanks of China for the action
                    of the United States in reference to the indemnity. Will probably leave early in
                    November.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Rockhill.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
